Query Modifiers

Source: R/query_modifiers.R
query_modifier.Rd

Helpers for use in constructing conditions in queries.

Usage

greater_than_(x, or_equal = FALSE)

less_than_(x, or_equal = FALSE)

between_(x, y, care = FALSE, negate = FALSE)

starts_with_(x, care = FALSE)

ends_with_(x)

contains_(x, care = FALSE)

like_(x)

in_(x, care = FALSE, negate = FALSE)

equals_(x, negate = FALSE)

# S3 method for class 'modifier'
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x, y

input

or_equal

<lgl> append =

care

<lgl> use uppercase operators for care endpoint

negate

<lgl> prepend NOT

...

additional arguments

Value

An object of class <modifier>

Details

Query modifiers are a small DSL for use in constructing query conditions, in the JSON-API format.

Examples

greater_than_(1000)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: >
#> Value(s): 1000
#> Allowed: [caid][care][hgov][open][prov]
greater_than_(0.125, or_equal = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: >=
#> Value(s): 0.125
#> Allowed: [caid][care][hgov][open][prov]
less_than_(1000)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: <
#> Value(s): 1000
#> Allowed: [caid][care][hgov][open][prov]
less_than_(0.125, or_equal = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: <=
#> Value(s): 0.125
#> Allowed: [caid][care][hgov][open][prov]
between_(1000, 1100)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: between
#> Value(s): 1000 and 1100
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
between_(0.125, 2, negate = TRUE) # should ignore `negate`
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: between
#> Value(s): 0.125 and 2
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
between_(0.125, 2, care = TRUE, negate = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: NOT+BETWEEN
#> Value(s): 0.125 and 2
#> Allowed: [care]
starts_with_("foo")
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: starts+with
#> Value(s): foo
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
starts_with_("foo", care = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: STARTS_WITH
#> Value(s): foo
#> Allowed: [care]
ends_with_("bar")
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: ENDS_WITH
#> Value(s): bar
#> Allowed: [care]
contains_("baz")
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: contains
#> Value(s): baz
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
contains_("baz", care = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: CONTAINS
#> Value(s): baz
#> Allowed: [care]
like_("baz")
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: like
#> Value(s): baz
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
in_(state.abb[10:15])
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: in
#> Value(s): GA, HI, ID, IL, IN, and IA
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
in_(state.abb[10:15], negate = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: not+in
#> Value(s): GA, HI, ID, IL, IN, and IA
#> Allowed: [caid][hgov][open][prov]
in_(state.abb[1:5], care = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: IN
#> Value(s): AL, AK, AZ, AR, and CA
#> Allowed: [care]
in_(state.abb[1:5], care = TRUE, negate = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: NOT+IN
#> Value(s): AL, AK, AZ, AR, and CA
#> Allowed: [care]
equals_(1000)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: =
#> Value(s): 1000
#> Allowed: [caid][care][hgov][open][prov]
equals_(1000, negate = TRUE)
#> <modifier>
#> Operator: <>
#> Value(s): 1000
#> Allowed: [caid][care][hgov][open][prov]
